1.01	Corton_(meat_spread)	Cretons	In Quebec cuisine, cretons (sometimes gorton or corton, especially among New Englanders of Quebec origin) is a pork spread containing onions and spices. Due to its fatty texture and taste, it resembles French rillettes. Cretons are usually served on toast as part of a traditional Quebec breakfast. Not to be confused with tête fromagée or head cheese.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d9/Creton_du_Porc.jpg/220px-Creton_du_Porc.jpg
